Package: CppDebugHelper
Title: Functions for debuggers like 'gdb' to inspect R- and Rcpp-specific types in C and C++ based code called from R
Version: 0.1
Date: 2019-10-26
Authors@R: c(
  person("Juergen", "Altfeld", email = "jaltfeld@altfeld-im.de", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
  )
Description: This packages provides functions that can be called from a debugger (eg. gdb)
             to easily inspect (print) the content of R and Rcpp specific data types like variables or environments
             on the console when debugging C or C++ called called from R.
             This can be done without modifying the source code of the debugged code.
License: GPL-3 + FILE LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/aryoda/CppDebugHelper
BugReports: https://github.com/aryoda/CppDebugHelper/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
